{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":843,"text":"I'd like to show you a video of some of the models"},{"time":2888,"text":"I work with."},{"time":4477,"text":"They're all the perfect size, and they don't have an ounce of fat."},{"time":8015,"text":"Did I mention they're gorgeous?"},{"time":10553,"text":"And they're scientific models? (Laughs)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":13683,"text":"As you might have guessed, I'm a tissue engineer,"},{"time":16026,"text":"and this is a video of some of the beating heart"},{"time":18475,"text":"that I've engineered in the lab."},{"time":20691,"text":"And one day we hope that these tissues"},{"time":22573,"text":"can serve as replacement parts for the human body."},{"time":25517,"text":"But what I'm going to tell you about today"},{"time":27797,"text":"is how these tissues make awesome models."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32244,"text":"Well, let's think about the drug screening process for a moment."},{"time":34971,"text":"You go from drug formulation, lab testing, animal testing,"},{"time":37949,"text":"and then clinical trials, which you might call human testing,"},{"time":40452,"text":"before the drugs get to market."},{"time":42717,"text":"It costs a lot of money, a lot of time,"},{"time":45860,"text":"and sometimes, even when a drug hits the market,"},{"time":48670,"text":"it acts in an unpredictable way and actually hurts people."},{"time":52605,"text":"And the later it fails, the worse the consequences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56692,"text":"It all boils down to two issues. One, humans are not rats,"},{"time":60876,"text":"and two, despite our incredible similarities to one another,"},{"time":64964,"text":"actually those tiny differences between you and I"},{"time":67405,"text":"have huge impacts with how we metabolize drugs"},{"time":69914,"text":"and how those drugs affect us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71783,"text":"So what if we had better models in the lab"},{"time":74615,"text":"that could not only mimic us better than rats"},{"time":77885,"text":"but also reflect our diversity?"},{"time":81805,"text":"Let's see how we can do it with tissue engineering."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85732,"text":"One of the key technologies that's really important"},{"time":88261,"text":"is what's called induced pluripotent stem cells."},{"time":91453,"text":"They were developed in Japan pretty recently."},{"time":93971,"text":"Okay, induced pluripotent stem cells."},{"time":96418,"text":"They're a lot like embryonic stem cells"},{"time":98531,"text":"except without the controversy."},{"time":100748,"text":"We induce cells, okay, say, skin cells,"},{"time":103647,"text":"by adding a few genes to them, culturing them,"},{"time":106154,"text":"and then harvesting them."},{"time":107775,"text":"So they're skin cells that can be tricked,"},{"time":110482,"text":"kind of like cellular amnesia, into an embryonic state."},{"time":113266,"text":"So without the controversy, that's cool thing number one."},{"time":115978,"text":"Cool thing number two, you can grow any type of tissue"},{"time":118527,"text":"out of them: brain, heart, liver, you get the picture,"},{"time":121082,"text":"but out of your cells."},{"time":123605,"text":"So we can make a model of your heart, your brain"},{"time":127170,"text":"on a chip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129802,"text":"Generating tissues of predictable density and behavior"},{"time":132658,"text":"is the second piece, and will be really key towards"},{"time":135490,"text":"getting these models to be adopted for drug discovery."},{"time":138162,"text":"And this is a schematic of a bioreactor we're developing in our lab"},{"time":141274,"text":"to help engineer tissues in a more modular, scalable way."},{"time":144722,"text":"Going forward, imagine a massively parallel version of this"},{"time":148121,"text":"with thousands of pieces of human tissue."},{"time":150458,"text":"It would be like having a clinical trial on a chip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154506,"text":"But another thing about these induced pluripotent stem cells"},{"time":158301,"text":"is that if we take some skin cells, let's say,"},{"time":160850,"text":"from people with a genetic disease"},{"time":163026,"text":"and we engineer tissues out of them,"},{"time":165282,"text":"we can actually use tissue-engineering techniques"},{"time":167250,"text":"to generate models of those diseases in the lab."},{"time":170651,"text":"Here's an example from Kevin Eggan's lab at Harvard."},{"time":174235,"text":"He generated neurons"},{"time":176525,"text":"from these induced pluripotent stem cells"},{"time":179240,"text":"from patients who have Lou Gehrig's Disease,"},{"time":181869,"text":"and he differentiated them into neurons, and what's amazing"},{"time":184312,"text":"is that these neurons also show symptoms of the disease."},{"time":187464,"text":"So with disease models like these, we can fight back"},{"time":189563,"text":"faster than ever before and understand the disease better"},{"time":192145,"text":"than ever before, and maybe discover drugs even faster."},{"time":196108,"text":"This is another example of patient-specific stem cells"},{"time":199488,"text":"that were engineered from someone with retinitis pigmentosa."},{"time":203497,"text":"This is a degeneration of the retina."},{"time":205251,"text":"It's a disease that runs in my family, and we really hope"},{"time":208008,"text":"that cells like these will help us find a cure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210232,"text":"So some people think that these models sound well and good,"},{"time":213040,"text":"but ask, \"Well, are these really as good as the rat?\""},{"time":216481,"text":"The rat is an entire organism, after all,"},{"time":219469,"text":"with interacting networks of organs."},{"time":221175,"text":"A drug for the heart can get metabolized in the liver,"},{"time":225096,"text":"and some of the byproducts may be stored in the fat."},{"time":227936,"text":"Don't you miss all that with these tissue-engineered models?"},{"time":232463,"text":"Well, this is another trend in the field."},{"time":234577,"text":"By combining tissue engineering techniques with microfluidics,"},{"time":237444,"text":"the field is actually evolving towards just that,"},{"time":239608,"text":"a model of the entire ecosystem of the body,"},{"time":242114,"text":"complete with multiple organ systems to be able to test"},{"time":244514,"text":"how a drug you might take for your blood pressure"},{"time":246117,"text":"might affect your liver or an antidepressant might affect your heart."},{"time":249384,"text":"These systems are really hard to build, but we're just starting to be able to get there,"},{"time":253456,"text":"and so, watch out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256760,"text":"But that's not even all of it, because once a drug is approved,"},{"time":259392,"text":"tissue engineering techniques can actually help us develop more personalized treatments."},{"time":263074,"text":"This is an example that you might care about someday,"},{"time":266816,"text":"and I hope you never do,"},{"time":268936,"text":"because imagine if you ever get that call"},{"time":271456,"text":"that gives you that bad news that you might have cancer."},{"time":274664,"text":"Wouldn't you rather test to see if those cancer drugs"},{"time":277200,"text":"you're going to take are going to work on your cancer?"},{"time":279960,"text":"This is an example from Karen Burg's lab, where they're"},{"time":282382,"text":"using inkjet technologies to print breast cancer cells"},{"time":285288,"text":"and study its progressions and treatments."},{"time":287759,"text":"And some of our colleagues at Tufts are mixing models"},{"time":290312,"text":"like these with tissue-engineered bone to see how cancer"},{"time":293400,"text":"might spread from one part of the body to the next,"},{"time":296120,"text":"and you can imagine those kinds of multi-tissue chips"},{"time":298504,"text":"to be the next generation of these kinds of studies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301489,"text":"And so thinking about the models that we've just discussed,"},{"time":303911,"text":"you can see, going forward, that tissue engineering"},{"time":305824,"text":"is actually poised to help revolutionize drug screening"},{"time":308280,"text":"at every single step of the path:"},{"time":311058,"text":"disease models making for better drug formulations,"},{"time":313632,"text":"massively parallel human tissue models helping to revolutionize lab testing,"},{"time":317503,"text":"reduce animal testing and human testing in clinical trials,"},{"time":321728,"text":"and individualized therapies that disrupt"},{"time":323420,"text":"what we even consider to be a market at all."},{"time":327008,"text":"Essentially, we're dramatically speeding up that feedback"},{"time":329552,"text":"between developing a molecule and learning about"},{"time":331875,"text":"how it acts in the human body."},{"time":334224,"text":"Our process for doing this is essentially transforming"},{"time":336552,"text":"biotechnology and pharmacology into an information technology,"},{"time":341413,"text":"helping us discover and evaluate drugs faster,"},{"time":344392,"text":"more cheaply and more effectively."},{"time":347608,"text":"It gives new meaning to models against animal testing, doesn't it?"},{"time":351688,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}